Hi All,

Every time we upload code and enable teleop our swerve steer motors (Mk4i swerves, all Neos), do a few full rotations then stop and stay steady.

We thought it might have something to do with the IMU (Pigeon 2) booting and calibrating, but moving the initialization of the Pigeon to our robot init section, so that it boots and calibrates before we even get to auto or teleop did not seem to fix the problem. Has anyone else seen a problem like this?

We are using the WPI template for our swerve code.

Thanks,
Will

we’ve had this issue, it’s usually caused by the cancoders not booting before their reading is taken. this can be remedied by setting the cancoders to only read when enabled, or to put a second or so delay between instantiation and reading of them. Our code which has the problem fixed can be seen here. (it’s a port of BaseTalonFX Swerve to neos, ported from 3512’s 2022 code – it’s still running Phoenix but we’re getting to that eventually – or not because it’s only for the cancoders and doesn’t need to be changed really.)
